title: Egypt's President Sisi visits General Intelligence Service headquarters - Politics - Egypt
text:
Related El-Sisi visits General Intelligence Service headquarters Egypt President appoints new acting head of intelligence agency Egyptian President Abdel-Fattah El-Sisi visited earlier on Thursday the headquarters of Egyptâ€™s General Intelligence Service in Cairo, Ahram Arabic news website reported.
During his visit, El-Sisi met with the head of the General Intelligence Service, Khaled Fawzi.
The president also held a meeting with other leading officials in the General Intelligence Service to discuss the latest challenges facing the country, as well the most recent developments in the region and their affects on Egypt's national security.
